    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A group of investors led by Wilbur Ross will sell a substantial share of its stake in an Osaka-based lender, Kansai Sawayaka Bank Ltd., to the Bank of Kansai Ltd. The two banks will then merge in two years. Bank of Kansai is 49 percent owned by the Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corporation, which is trying to strengthen its operations in Osaka, Japan's second-largest city. An investment fund led by Mr. Ross opened Kansai Sawayaka Bank in February 2001 after taking over Kofuku Bank, which was in bankruptcy.</p>
        <p>Ken Belson (NYT)</p>
      </block>
